Day 42 of Circuit Breaker.⁣
⁣
【With Recipe 🦑 】

Friends sometimes say that I am blur like sotong. 🦑 But when it comes to short cut in cooking and still yield good result, I am not blur lah. 😂 Easy peasy Sambal Sotong (Squid) using store bought sambal paste. 😝⁣
⁣
Posting together with @thegaring.ig for this week Sambal theme. #thegaring266⁣
⁣
Here is my easy peasy recipe. ⁣
⁣
Sambal Sotong (Squid) 叁峇苏东⁣
𝕀𝕟𝕘𝕣𝕖𝕕𝕚𝕖𝕟𝕥𝕤⁣
2 pcs of sotongs (squids), cut into rings⁣
1 tbsp cooking oil⁣
2 cloves minced garlic⁣
2 shallots, sliced⁣
11/2 tsp Sambal Belachan Chili (add more if you like spicy)⁣
Some pink salt
⁣
𝕊𝕥𝕖𝕡𝕤:⁣
1. Heat up the cooking in a wok.  Add garlic and shallots and fry. Stir till fragrant and becomes soft.⁣
2. Add the sotongs(squids) and stir briefly. ⁣
3. Add sambal paste and some water. Sprinkles some pink salt. Stir the sambal with the sotongs(squids) till well combined and the squids are cooked. ⁣
4. Dish and serve hot.⁣
⁣
